@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{codex-extras.el} extends the @samp{codex} package with additional functionality for working with the OpenAI Codex CLI from within Emacs.  It is the Codex counterpart to @samp{claude-code-extras.el}, providing a similar set of conveniences for session management, theme synchronization, skill execution, project auditing, and debugging. @*

The package builds on @samp{ai-extras.el} (@ref{Top,ai-extras,,ai-extras,}) for shared functionality such as the unified session switcher, home-row key assignments, buffer protection, notifications, snippet expansion, and terminal fixes.  Codex-specific features include theme synchronization with Codex's TOML configuration, a skill runner that discovers skills from Codex's @samp{.agents/skills/} directories, and notification handling for Codex CLI hook events. @*

At load time, @samp{codex-extras.el} registers the Codex backend with @samp{ai-extras.el} and installs hooks on @code{codex-start-hook}, @code{codex-event-hook}, and standard Emacs hooks to integrate all features automatically.  The backend icon is the official Codex terminal-prompt logo rendered as an inline SVG via @code{ai-extras-svg-icon} (@ref{h:svg-icons,SVG icons,,ai-extras,}). @*

