@node Theme synchronization
@section Theme synchronization

@vindex codex-extras-sync-theme
The user option @code{codex-extras-sync-theme} controls whether Emacs theme changes are propagated to Codex.  When non-@code{nil}, switching between light and dark Emacs themes updates the @samp{tui.theme} key in @samp{~/.codex/config.toml} and sends the @samp{/theme} command to all running Codex sessions.  The default is @code{nil}. @*

@node Session handoff
@section Session handoff

@vindex codex-extras-handoff-file
The user option @code{codex-extras-handoff-file} specifies the path to the handoff file used by @code{codex-extras-handoff} ([BROKEN LINK: h:handoff-command]).  The default is @samp{/tmp/codex-handoff.md}.  The handoff skill writes session transition instructions to this file before the command reads them. @*

@node Skill runner
@section Skill runner

@vindex codex-extras-skill-directories
The user option @code{codex-extras-skill-directories} specifies additional directories to scan for Codex skills, beyond the standard locations (@samp{~/.codex/skills/} and the project's @samp{.agents/skills/}). @*

@vindex codex-extras-run-skill-model
The user option @code{codex-extras-run-skill-model} overrides the model used when running skills via @code{codex-extras-run-skill}.  The default is @code{nil}, which uses the CLI's default model. @*

@node Project audit
@section Project audit

@vindex codex-extras-audit-skills
The user option @code{codex-extras-audit-skills} lists the skills invoked by @code{codex-extras-audit-project} ([BROKEN LINK: h:audit-command]).  The default includes @samp{/code-audit}, @samp{/design-audit}, and @samp{/interpretability-audit}.  Each skill is sent with the @samp{--accept} flag for non-interactive execution. @*

@vindex codex-extras-audit-project-directories
The user option @code{codex-extras-audit-project-directories} provides completion candidates for the project audit directory prompt.  New directories entered by the user are automatically persisted to this list. @*

@node Debug backtrace
@section Debug backtrace

@vindex codex-extras-debug-backtrace-model
The user option @code{codex-extras-debug-backtrace-model} specifies the @samp{gptel} model used to analyze Emacs backtraces and identify the culprit package.  The default is @code{gemini-flash-lite-latest}, a fast model suitable for this classification task. @*

@vindex codex-extras-debug-backtrace-backend
The user option @code{codex-extras-debug-backtrace-backend} specifies the @samp{gptel} backend name for backtrace analysis.  The default is @samp{"Gemini"}. @*

