@node Session management
@section Session management

@findex codex-extras-start-or-switch
The command @code{codex-extras-start-or-switch} starts a new Codex session or opens the unified session switcher.  When no Codex sessions are active, it calls @code{codex} to start a new one.  When sessions exist, it delegates to the @samp{ai-extras} session switcher (@ref{h:session-management,Session management,,ai-extras,}), which displays all AI sessions (including Claude Code sessions, if any) with home-row key bindings. @*

@findex codex-extras-handoff
The command @code{codex-extras-handoff} closes the current Codex session and starts a new one with the handoff prompt.  The handoff skill must have been run first to write the handoff file at @code{codex-extras-handoff-file} (@ref{Session handoff}).  The new session starts in the same project directory as the closed one, with the handoff contents passed as a CLI argument. @*

@findex codex-extras-restart
The command @code{codex-extras-restart} kills the current Codex session and resumes it in place.  This is useful when a setting change requires relaunching Codex.  The new session preserves the directory and instance name, and resumes via @samp{codex resume --last}, which Codex CLI filters by the current working directory; since the just-killed session is the most recently updated one for that directory, Codex re-opens it.  If multiple Codex sessions share the same directory, Codex picks whichever was most recently written. @*

@node Tool execution
@section Tool execution

@findex codex-extras-run-skill
The command @code{codex-extras-run-skill} discovers available Codex skills, prompts the user to select one with completion, optionally prompts for arguments, and sends the skill invocation to the active Codex session.  Skills are discovered from @samp{~/.codex/skills/}, the project's @samp{.agents/skills/} directory, and any directories in @code{codex-extras-skill-directories} (@ref{Skill runner}). @*

@findex codex-extras-audit-project
The command @code{codex-extras-audit-project} runs a comprehensive audit of a project directory.  It prompts for a directory (with completion from @code{codex-extras-audit-project-directories}), then sequentially sends each skill in @code{codex-extras-audit-skills} to a Codex session in that directory.  Each skill is invoked with @samp{--accept} for non-interactive execution.  If no existing Codex session is found, the command creates one; if session creation fails, it signals an error. @*

@node Debugging
@section Debugging

@findex codex-extras-debug-backtrace
The command @code{codex-extras-debug-backtrace} automates the workflow of debugging an Emacs error.  When invoked from the @samp{*Backtrace*} buffer, it saves the backtrace, sends it to a lightweight LLM (via @samp{gptel}) to identify candidate packages, presents the candidates via @code{completing-read}, then starts a Codex session in the selected package's source directory with instructions to fix the bug. @*

The LLM backend and model are configured via @code{codex-extras-debug-backtrace-backend} and @code{codex-extras-debug-backtrace-model} (@ref{Debug backtrace}). @*

@node Buffer management
@section Buffer management

@findex codex-extras-setup-kill-on-exit
The command @code{codex-extras-setup-kill-on-exit} wraps the process sentinel so that the buffer is automatically killed when the Codex process exits.  This is called automatically on session startup via @code{codex-start-hook}. @*

@node Mode line integration
@chapter Mode line integration

@findex codex-extras-status-model
@findex codex-extras-status-duration-ms
The package provides helpers used by the @samp{doom-modeline} @samp{ai-session} segment.  @code{codex-extras-status-model} returns the model declared in @samp{~/.codex/config.toml}, and @code{codex-extras-status-duration-ms} returns the running session's elapsed time in milliseconds (or @code{nil} outside a Codex session). @*

@vindex codex-extras--config-model-cache
The status helper caches the model lookup in @code{codex-extras--config-model-cache}, keyed by the configuration file's modification time.  This avoids re-reading @samp{~/.codex/config.toml} from disk on every modeline redraw — a hot path that is evaluated on every keystroke when a Codex buffer is current.  The cache invalidates automatically the next time the file is touched. @*

@node Transient menus
@chapter Transient menus

@findex ai-extras-menu
All @samp{codex-extras} commands are accessible through the unified @code{ai-extras-menu} (@ref{h:transient-menu,ai-extras menu,,ai-extras,}).  Codex-specific entries (such as the theme sync toggle) are appended to the shared menu at load time.  The menu is organized into columns: @*

@itemize
@item
@strong{Sessions}: start or switch, handoff, restart. @*
@item
@strong{Tools}: run skill, audit project, debug backtrace. @*
@item
@strong{Alerts}: toggle alert notifications. @*
@item
@strong{Buffer}: setup kill on exit, fix rendering, disable scrollback. @*
@item
@strong{Options}: toggle boolean settings (alert on ready, protect buffers, sync theme). @*
@end itemize

